1.Why you shouldn't use equality operator to compare float values?
Because the smallest rounding error will cause two floating point numbers to not be equal.


2.What is the preferred way to compare two float values?
Float are useful when you need fractional value, it is not preferred to use in large values.


3.What should be the criteria to define range value that should be used to compare two float values?
Up to 1-3 precision digit number would be best for compare two floating value. We can use suffix for compare two float number.


4.What is the use of strictfp?
It is a keyword in java, and it is used to ensure the portability of floating point number after calculation.